## Asking a Question

### The empty state

When you open the Help panel with no active conversation, you see:

- The heading **"Ask anything about Graphium"** with the subtext *"Get quick answers from Graphium docs without leaving your workflow."*
- Four **suggested questions** as clickable chips — for example, *"How do I create a vault?"*, *"What are connections?"*, *"What is the AI Assistant?"*, and *"How do I invite teammates?"*

Click any suggested question to send it immediately, or type your own question in the input box.

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/reference/ask-help-question.png" alt="Help panel empty state showing suggested questions" />
</Frame>

---

### Typing and sending a message

1. Click the **"Ask a question..."** input at the bottom of the panel.
2. Type your question in plain language — for example, *"How do I add a connection to my vault?"* or *"What is a schema property?"*
3. Press **Enter** or click the **send button** (arrow icon) to submit.

The assistant begins streaming a response immediately. You can see the response building in real time as it is generated.

> **Note:** The Help Assistant only supports text questions. File, photo, and link attachments are not supported.

---

### Reading a response

Responses appear under the **Graphium Help** label and support full markdown formatting — headings, numbered lists, bold text, code blocks, and inline links.

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/reference/help-question-response.png" alt="Help panel showing an assistant response with markdown formatting and source citations" />
</Frame>

---

### Source citations

Where available, each assistant response includes a **Sources** section below the message. Sources appear as clickable chips — each one shows the title of the relevant documentation article. Click a source chip to open the full article.

