## When the Help Assistant Is Unavailable

In some situations the Help Assistant may not be available. When this happens, the panel displays an informational message before you start typing — you will not be able to send questions until the issue resolves.

| Situation | What you see |
|-----------|-------------|
| The assistant service is temporarily unavailable | A message indicating the assistant is unavailable and to try again later |
| You have sent too many questions in a short period | A message indicating you have reached the usage limit for your session, with guidance to wait before trying again |
| The assistant is not yet configured for your environment | A message indicating the help feature is not currently available |

If you see one of these states, closing and reopening the panel may resolve it if the issue was temporary. For persistent unavailability, contact your workspace Admin or [support@graphium.ai](mailto:support@graphium.ai).

