## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Likely Cause | What to Do |
|-------|--------------|------------|
| Help icon is not visible in the header | You may not be signed in to a workspace | Sign in and navigate to your workspace — the help icon appears in the global header once authenticated |
| Panel opens but shows "unavailable" message | The help service is temporarily down or not configured | Try again in a few minutes; if the issue persists, contact support |
| Response stopped mid-sentence | You may have closed and reopened the panel while a response was streaming, or there was a connection interruption | Click **+ New conversation** and ask your question again |
| My previous conversation is gone | The page was refreshed, you logged out, or you switched workspaces | Help conversations are session-only — they do not persist across page loads or account changes |
| I sent a question but got no response | Your question may have been blocked, or you may have reached the usage limit | Check for a rate limit message in the panel; if none is shown, try rephrasing and resending |
| The keyboard shortcut is not working | Another application or browser shortcut may be intercepting it | Click the ? icon in the header directly to open the panel |

